1. Basic Retrieval Queries

a. Find the names of all vehicles manufactured by Toyota.

b. Find all vehicles manufactured between 2010 and 2020.

c. Find all vehicles that do not use Gasoline fuel.

d. Find all vehicles whose Engine_CC is greater than 3000.

e. Find all vehicles with exactly 8 cylinders.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Basic Retrieval & Filtering Queries

a-Find the make names for all vehicles manufactured by Toyota.

Find the make names of vehicles manufactured between 2010 and 2020

c.Find the make names of vehicles that do not use gasoline fuel.

d.Find the make names of vehicles whose Engine_CC is greater than 3000.

e. Find the make names of vehicles with exactly 8 cylinders.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Join Queries

a. Find the vehicle display names along with their make names.

b. Find all vehicles with their corresponding fuel type names.

c. Find all vehicles with their body type names.

d. Find all vehicles along with their drive type names.

e. Find all vehicles with make, model, and submodel names.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Aggregate Queries

a. Find the total number of vehicles in the database.

b. Find the number of vehicles for each make.

c. Find the average Engine_CC for each make.

d. Find the maximum Engine_CC for each fuel type.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Subquery Practice

a. Find all vehicles with Engine_CC greater than the average Engine_CC.

b. Find all vehicles with the maximum Engine_CC.

c. Find vehicles whose Engine_CC is one of the top 5 highest values.

d. Find vehicles with FuelTypeID belonging to the most common fuel type.

e. Find makes whose vehicle count is greater than the average vehicle count per make.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. Correlated Subqueries

a. Find vehicles whose Engine_CC is greater than the average Engine_CC of their make.

b. Find vehicles that have the highest Engine_CC within their make.

c. Find vehicles manufactured in the latest year for each make.

d. Find vehicles whose cylinder count is above the average for their fuel type.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6. EXISTS / NOT EXISTS

a. Find makes that have at least one vehicle.

b. Find fuel types that are not used by any vehicle.

c. Find body types that have at least one vehicle.

d. Find models that are not referenced by any vehicle.

e. Find the minimum Engine_CC for each body type.
